class.description:
[BlaziumGoapAction] represents a single capability of an AI entity. The planner chains actions together if their [member effects] satisfy another action's [member preconditions] in order to reach the current goal. Action validity and costs can be modified dynamically via GDScript overrides.
Example usage:
[codeblock]
class_name GatherWood extends BlaziumGoapAction
func _init():
    set_name("GatherWood")
    cost = 1
    effects = {"has_wood": true}

func _perform(_delta: float) -> bool:
    # Returning true indicates the action completed successfully.
    return true
[/codeblock]
[codeblock]
class_name BuildCampfire extends BlaziumGoapAction
func _init():
    set_name("BuildCampfire")
    cost = 2
    preconditions = {"has_wood": true}
    effects = {"has_campfire": true}

func _perform(_delta: float) -> bool:
    return true
[/codeblock]
